# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .gitignore — WCS-Gateway (.NET 8)
# Build output & IDE/local state must NOT be tracked.
# Source, configs, docs, .agents/.claude tooling ARE tracked.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Build output (per-project)
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Oo]ut/
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/

# Visual Studio / Rider / VS Code local state
.vs/
.vscode/
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
.idea/

# Build/test artifacts
*.dll
*.exe
*.pdb
*.cache
project.assets.json
*.nuget.cache
*.nuget.dgspec.json
staticwebassets*.json
*.staticwebassets.endpoints.json

# Local runtime data (e.g. wcs-mcp SQLite DB) — never source
data/*.db
data/*.db-shm
data/*.db-wal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# OS junk
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# ── Intentionally KEPT (not ignored) ────────────────────────
# - WcsSystem/Wcs.PlcService/Config/db500-keys.json   (DB500 catalog, source of truth)
# - WcsSystem/Wcs.PlcService/Plc/Db500Map.g.cs         (generated but committed catalog output)
# - tools/Db500MapGen/                                  (generator)
# - document.md, CLAUDE.md, .agents/, .claude/, .mcp.json
# Db500Map.g.cs lives under Plc/ (not obj/), so the obj/ rule does NOT hide it.
